jQuery.media plugin

2012. Created by Oscar Otero (http://oscarotero.com / http://anavallasuiza.com)

JQuery.media is a jQuery plugin that allows manage html5 video and audio elements: properties, events, etc.

Available plugins:
jquery.media.timeline: allows synchronize content with the timeline of the video/audio
jquery.media.tracks: allows synchronize webSrt files (subtitles, chapters, descriptions, etc) with video and audio elements
jquery.media.tocanvas: export the video to canvas and allowing pixel manipulation in real time
jquery.media.sync: allows synchronize two or more media elements

Example:

//Create a media element
var video = $.media('#my-video');

video.seek(3); //Goes to second 3
video.seek('00:03'); //Goes to second 3

video.play(function () {
	alert('This is a play event!');
});

video.play(); //Plays the video (and trigger the play event)

More info and examples in http://idc.anavallasuiza.com/project/jquerymedia/

